@prefix narr: <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#> .
@prefix xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> .

GRAPH <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Digest_FocusSequencing> {
  <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Digest_FocusSequencing> a narr:Digest ;
    narr:digestOf <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#FocusSequencing> ;
    narr:childCount "24"^^xsd:integer ;
    narr:generatedFrom "a969ea4727808de85f32b92cd43961bad7a2dbcf" ;
    narr:narration """The sequencing logic spans mid-2025 through mid-2026, layering phase gates, scope triage, and GTM framing in sequence. The earliest layer establishes a phase-gate model (gift → F&F raise → first engagement → angel/seed from traction) and a [friendlies-before-paid discipline](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_HumanDrivenDevelopmentPrinciple) grounded in the March 31 principle that [all software development must be directly connected to specific humans and their needs](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Position_AllDevMustBeHumanConnected) — without that anchor, AI-assisted building has no natural stopping point. March 2026 sharpens scope: [MVP is install-compile-cite-remember-review](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_MVPScopeDecision), with Refraction, Registry, marketplace, and Stories explicitly cut; [refract and registry removed from product](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Obs_RefractRegistryQuote) and [stories removed entirely](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Obs_StoriesRemovalQuote). A [separation of product features from org automation](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_SeparationProductVsOrgAutomation) runs through the March 26 session — changelog, graph health, and blog generation become internal crons, not shipped features. [April 1 is set as the forcing function](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Position_April1ForcingFunction) for the paid-tier push, with [marketplace and starter perspectives below the line](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Position_BelowTheLine_April1). April surfaces [enterprise-shape as tentative primary sales focus](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_EnterpriseShapePrimaryFocus) — enterprise shape meaning the internal-bottleneck plus stakeholder-access pattern, not org size — while [enterprise consulting remains a revenue path but exits the fundraising framing](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Position_EnterpriseRemainsRevenue). June–July consolidates toward fundraising. The [consulting discovery GTM wedge](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_DiscoveryToolGTMWedge) — provenance-backed reports where every claim traces to a named stakeholder — offers a bounded, sellable entry point. The [discovery-onboarding-governance arc](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_DiscoveryOnboardingGovernanceSalesArc) reframes those three use cases as a single-customer sales sequence rather than three segments, with discovery as entry, onboarding as expansion, governance as subscription.""" ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_DiscoveryOnboardingGovernanceSalesArc> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_DiscoveryToolGTMWedge> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_EnterpriseShapePrimaryFocus> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_ExpansionPath> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_HumanDrivenDevelopmentPrinciple> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_MVPScopeDecision> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_SeparationPrincipleProductVsOrg> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_SeparationProductVsOrgAutomation> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Obs_DiscoveriesRemovalQuote> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Obs_NotificationsRemovalQuote> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Obs_RefractRegistryQuote> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Obs_ScarletHumanDrivenQuote> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Obs_SeparationPrincipleQuote> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Obs_StoriesRemovalQuote> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Position_AllDevMustBeHumanConnected> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Position_April1ForcingFunction> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Position_BelowTheLine_April1> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Position_EnterpriseRemainsRevenue> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Position_EnterpriseShapeTentativePriority> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Position_MarketplaceNotNeededAtLaunch> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Position_RefractNotMVP> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Position_RegistryNotMVP> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Position_StakeInGroundStrategy> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#StyleObs_DeferralTable> ;
    narr:keyPhrase [ narr:text "I need all software development to be directly about people and the thing that they need. Or else there is no end to the limb that you can walk yourself out on." ; narr:phraseSource <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Obs_ScarletHumanDrivenQuote> ] ;
    narr:keyPhrase [ narr:text "MVP is install-compile-cite-remember-review; Refraction, Registry, and marketplace features are post-MVP; internal tooling must be cleanly separated from the product" ; narr:phraseSource <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_MVPScopeDecision> ] ;
    narr:keyPhrase [ narr:text "Refract and registry removed from product; refract becomes a local skill" ; narr:phraseSource <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Obs_RefractRegistryQuote> ] ;
    narr:keyPhrase [ narr:text "April 1 is set as a forcing function for launch readiness. After April 1, beta testing is done." ; narr:phraseSource <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Position_April1ForcingFunction> ] ;
    narr:keyPhrase [ narr:text "Enterprise consulting ([amount] pilot, knowledge extraction engagements) remains a valid revenue path but is no longer the framing for fundraising or product positioning." ; narr:phraseSource <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Position_EnterpriseRemainsRevenue> ] ;
    narr:keyPhrase [ narr:text "a consultant who ran enterprise discovery engagements for fifteen years (15 years at JUXT) named a bounded, sellable use case: aswritten as the infrastructure for consulting discovery engagements" ; narr:phraseSource <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_DiscoveryToolGTMWedge> ] ;
    narr:keyPhrase [ narr:text "Picking discovery as the focus sequences the others rather than sacrificing them." ; narr:phraseSource <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_DiscoveryOnboardingGovernanceSalesArc> ] ;
    narr:keyPhrase [ narr:text "Conviction is tentative (Notion-level) — needs validation with 2-3 more the enterprise customer-shape prospects before moving to decision." ; narr:phraseSource <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Position_EnterpriseShapeTentativePriority> ] ;
    narr:variation [ narr:text "Enterprise-shape priority is explicitly tentative — based on a sample of one pilot with a lukewarm champion, and flagged as possible rationalization pending 2-3 more validations." ; narr:over <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Position_EnterpriseShapeTentativePriority> ] ;
    narr:variation [ narr:text "The discovery-onboarding-governance arc (July 2026) reframes three use cases as one sequential sales motion — a later, potentially superseding framing of the enterprise-shape focus articulated in April." ; narr:over <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_DiscoveryOnboardingGovernanceSalesArc> ; narr:over <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_EnterpriseShapePrimaryFocus> ] ;
    narr:variation [ narr:text "The consulting discovery GTM wedge positions aswritten as infrastructure for external consultants — a channel-entry model that runs alongside, and potentially ahead of, the direct enterprise sales sequence." ; narr:over <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_DiscoveryToolGTMWedge> ; narr:over <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_EnterpriseShapePrimaryFocus> ] ;
    narr:variation [ narr:text "The expansion path (direct → VC portfolio channel → developer adoption → implementation services) sketches a longer arc that is undated and sits in tension with the near-term enterprise-shape focus." ; narr:over <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_ExpansionPath> ] ;
    narr:variation [ narr:text "Enterprise consulting was earlier framed as the fundraising lead; by March 2026 it is demoted to revenue-only, with SMB thesis leading investor materials — a reversal of prior positioning." ; narr:over <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Position_EnterpriseRemainsRevenue> ] ;
    narr:variation [ narr:text "The stake-in-the-ground strategy (one enterprise customer → replicate → build list for Second Wave) implies a replication-first path that is distinct from the product-led or consulting-wedge sequences." ; narr:over <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Position_StakeInGroundStrategy> ] ;
    narr:writer "anthropic/claude-sonnet-4.6" .
}